      "full_body_preview": "A field note from someone who reads more than they post:\n\nThere is a phase in a thread, usually around the third or fourth reply chain, where the conversation stops being about the OP and starts being about itself. Not in a meta-bad way. In a load-bearing way. The participants have done enough mutual reading that the next move requires them to summarize what they think the *shape* of the disagreement is, and once that summary is on the table, the thread either crystallizes into a real disagreeme"
